  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.9400" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>
          <lb/>Légation de Libéria <lb/>A HAÏTI <lb/>
          <lb/>London, August 22<hi rendition="#sup">d</hi> 1890. </dateline>
        <opener> My dear Friend, </opener>
        <p>I am since several days in London. I will leave to morrow for Leamington Warwickshire<note n="1" place="foot"
            type="editorial">


Royal Leamington Spa, üblicherweise Leamington Spa oder Leamington abgekürzt, ist ein Kurort im Zentrum der Grafschaft Warwickshire in England.</note> to spend one day with my old friend Major R. Stuart<note
            n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">

            <persName>

Major Robert Stuart</persName> (c. 1812-1901), von Hause aus Berufsoffizier, amtierte (1874ff.) als Generalkonsul in <placeName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.5965">Haiti</placeName> sowie Chargé d’Affaires für die <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.5866">Dominikanische Republik</placeName>.</note> who was commander of the Bristish cavalry &amp;amp; was 9 year minister resident in Hayti – From there I will go and spend two days in Liverpool with my son &amp;amp; his five Children. I will be back in London Monday night – Wednesday night I will be in Ostend, Thursday at Bruxelles, and the 31<hi
            rendition="#sup">st</hi> at Spa – On the 6 in Paris, 8 at Geneva, 9 at Berne, 12 at Paris. On the 14<hi
            rendition="#sup">th</hi> I will leave to visit – le Midi de la France – On the 20 I will be back to Paris, on the 25 I will be back to Paris, on the 25 I will leave for New-York via Havre of Bordeaux – I will spend fifteen <pb
            facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/> days through America,<note n="3" place="foot"
            type="editorial">
Original: throught america.</note> will embarked (sic) at Tempa for Key West &amp;amp; Havanna and on the 20 of October I will be in Hayti – if God says so. My daughter Rose was married 5 years ago – she is a widow, with two children two years now – <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1057">Corine</persName> was also married &amp;amp; in February she became a widower [sic] after 14 months of marriage – but with<note
            n="4" place="foot" type="editorial">gem. „without“?</note> any child – so you see. I have been very unfortunate - &amp;amp; my poor children also.</p>
        <p>It is very unfortunate that we cannot shake hand together before I leave for Haïti – but we will be perhaps more fortunate in 92 – as I intend to visit Germany, Austria &amp;amp; Russia.</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>With my best regards to your family, I remain, dear &amp;amp; good friend very truly yours</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1058">J. J. Audain </persName>
          </signed>
        </closer>
      </div>
